Khama Billiat lost control of his car after a tyre burst in the torrential rain that most of the country experienced over the long weekend. JOHANNESBURG - Kaizer Chiefs talisman Khama Billiat emerged unscathed from a car accident in Johannesburg over the Easter weekend and will be available for his side's match against Golden Arrows  on Tuesday evening. Billiat lost control of his car after a tyre burst in the torrential rain that most of the country experienced over the long weekend. The Chiefs star netted a cracking goal to help the Glamour Boys book a Nedbank Cup final spot against NFD side TS Galaxy in a 4-2 semifinal win over Chippa United in Port Elizabeth on Saturday. Billiat will feature against Arrows at the FNB Stadium on Tuesday night.